[ 3, 8, 5, 12, 16, 9, 20, 24, 28, 17, 16, 40, 22, 52, 56, 20, 64, 31, 76, 40 ] To give my motivation - I want to prove that algebra $M_2(\mathbb F_q)$ can be represented as ${a+bj}$ for $a,b$ belonging to $\mathbb F_{q^2}$ and multiplication given by Cayley-Dickson $$(a+bj)(c+dj)=ac+\bar db + (da+b\bar c)j,$$ where $j$ is matrix satisfying $\bar j=-j$ .

